data.name: Beef Stew with Gravy
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty and savory beef stew simmered to perfection, served with rich gravy for a comforting meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add diced onion and minced garlic, saut√© until soft.
Add beef stew meat, browning on all sides.
Sprinkle flour over the meat, stirring to coat.
Pour in beef broth and soy sauce, stirring well.
Add chopped carrots, cubed potatoes, bay leaves, thyme, salt, and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for about 1.5 to 2 hours, or until the beef is tender.
